## ARCHITECTURE
- Multi-tenant SaaS: every table has company_id
- Supabase RLS enforced on ALL tables
- User roles: admin | manager | viewer
- PDF ops run CLIENT-SIDE (pdf-lib, @react-pdf/renderer) — zero server cost
- All AI calls go through /app/api/ai/route.ts using DeepSeek V4 Flash

## NDT REPORT NUMBERING
FG-RT-[YEAR]-[SEQ]   → Radiography Testing
FG-UT-[YEAR]-[SEQ]   → Ultrasonic Testing
FG-MPI-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Magnetic Particle Testing
FG-DPI-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Dye Penetrant Testing
FG-PMI-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Positive Material Identification
FG-HT-[YEAR]-[SEQ]   → Hardness Testing
FG-PAUT-[YEAR]-[SEQ] → Phased Array UT
FG-UTTG-[YEAR]-[SEQ] → Ultrasonic Thickness Gauge
FG-WQT-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Welding Qualification Test
FG-INV-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Invoice
FG-QUO-[YEAR]-[SEQ]  → Quotation
FG-TS-[YEAR]-[SEQ]   → Timesheet

## CODING RULES
1. Always TypeScript with proper types — import from @/types
2. Server components by default; 'use client' only when needed
3. Supabase RLS on ALL database operations — never bypass
4. Never expose API keys client-side
5. Use shadcn/ui components first
6. Always handle loading + error states
7. PDF operations are client-side only
8. All AI calls use DeepSeek V4 Flash via lib/ai/deepseek.ts

## FILE STRUCTURE
src/
  app/
    (auth)/login, register
    (dashboard)/layout, page, documents, invoices, quotations,
                reports, timesheets, clients, emails, settings,
                equipment, personnel
    api/ai, email, summary, tender
  components/ui, pdf, documents, dashboard, reports
  lib/supabase, ai, pdf, email
  types/index.ts

